UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1546
1 city at a regular election. A candidate for a legislative body shall be a resident
2 of the city for not less than one (1) year prior to his or her election. His or her
3 term of office shall begin on the first day of January following his or her
4 election and shall be for two (2) years in cities with populations of less than
5 twelve thousand (12,000) as determined by the most recent federal decennial
6 census, and for four (4) years in cities with populations of twelve thousand
7 (12,000) or more as determined by the most recent federal decennial census,
8 except as provided by KRS 83A.050. A member shall be at least eighteen (18)
9 years of age, shall be a qualified voter in the city, and shall reside in the city
10 throughout his or her term of office.
11 (b) If a city crosses the twelve thousand (12,000) population threshold, either
12 through an increase or decrease in population, as determined by the most
13 recent federal decennial census, the adjusted terms of office shall take effect
14 at the next regular election after the conclusion of the term of office of the
15 legislative body members, as determined immediately prior to the most
16 recent federal decennial census.
17 (5) If one (1) or more vacancies on a legislative body occur in a way that one (1) or
18 more members remain seated, the remaining members shall within thirty (30) days
19 fill the vacancies one (1) at a time, giving each new appointee reasonable notice of
20 his or her selection as will enable him or her to meet and act with the remaining
21 members in making further appointments until all vacancies are filled. If vacancies
22 occur in a way that all seats become vacant, the Governor shall appoint qualified
23 persons to fill the vacancies sufficient to constitute a quorum. Remaining vacancies
24 shall be filled as provided in this section.
25 (6) If for any reason, any vacancy in the office of mayor or the legislative body is not
26 filled within thirty (30) days after it occurs, the Governor shall promptly fill the
27 vacancy by appointment of a qualified person who shall serve for the same period
Page 2 of 4
