UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1546
1 as if otherwise appointed.
2 (7) No vacancy by reason of voluntary resignation in the office of mayor or on a
3 legislative body shall occur unless a written resignation which specifies a
4 resignation date is tendered to the legislative body. The resignation may be
5 submitted through electronic mail if it originates from the official's electronic mail
6 address and includes also the official's handwritten signature. The resignation shall
7 be effective at the next regular or special meeting of the city legislative body
8 occurring on or after the date specified in the written letter of resignation. If a
9 resignation date is not specified, the written resignation shall be deemed to become
10 effective at the first regular or special meeting of the legislative body occurring on
11 or after its receipt.
12 (8) Pursuant to KRS 118.305(7), if a vacancy occurs which is required by law to be
13 filled temporarily by appointment, the legislative body or the Governor, whichever
14 is designated to make the appointment, shall immediately notify in writing both the
15 county clerk and the Secretary of State of the vacancy.
16 (9) Except in cities of the first class, any elected officer, in case of misconduct,
17 incapacity, or willful neglect in the performance of the duties of his or her office,
18 may be removed from office by a unanimous vote of the members of the legislative
19 body exclusive of any member to be removed, who shall not vote in the deliberation
20 of his or her removal. No elected officer shall be removed without having been
21 given the right to a full public hearing. The officer, if removed, shall have the right
22 to appeal to the Circuit Court of the county and the appeal shall be on the record.
23 No officer so removed shall be eligible to fill the office vacated before the
24 expiration of the term to which originally elected.
25 (10) Removal of an elected officer in cities of the first class shall be governed by the
26 provisions of KRS 83.660.
27 Section 2. The term of legislative body members of cities with populations of
